Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 31, 37. Name Mytion. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ALEX ABC 0171.21.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0685)
